OL,3,CUS state visit risk 'grasped in both
OL,4,Chands' by King, aide says
OL,6,FThe King "grasped in both hands" the
OL,7,F"risk and challenge" of the US state
OL,8,Fvisit but will not dwell on the
OL,9,Fperceived success of his trip, a
OL,10,Fsenior palace aide has said.
OL,12,FThe "high-stakes" address to Congress
OL,13,Fwas one of a number of hurdles Charles
OL,14,Fovercame during his sternest
OL,15,Fdiplomatic test to date, but it was
OL,16,Falso seen as an opportunity to deliver
OL,17,Fon palace objectives in support of the
OL,18,FGovernment who requested the trip.
OL,26,@nD@JOUnD@`O]oD@AOUoD@TO]tD@EOUtD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/15
