OL,3,CUS state visit risk 'grasped in both
OL,4,Chands' by King, aide says
OL,6,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey
OL,7,Fvoiced concerns about Charles being
OL,8,Fembarrassed by Mr Trump and repeatedly
OL,9,Fcalled for the trip to be cancelled.
OL,11,FA senior palace aide said: "What
OL,12,Flooked like risk and challenge was
OL,13,Falso a phenomenal opportunity. One
OL,14,Fthat was grasped in both hands by the
OL,15,FKing and we shall leave you to
OL,16,Fconclude what the outcome of that was.
OL,26,@sD@\OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
