OL,3,CUS state visit risk 'grasped in both
OL,4,Chands' by King, aide says
OL,6,F"He's not a man to dwell long on what
OL,7,Fsome may consider yesterday's
OL,8,Fsuccesses, he is always looking
OL,9,Ftowards tomorrow's opportunities, so
OL,10,Fgenerally we've tried to encourage him
OL,11,Fto feel positive ` and he has ` about
OL,12,Fthe way that the American leg in
OL,13,Fparticular has gone in particular, but
OL,14,Fhis mind is already on what he can
OL,15,Fachieve next rather than what he
OL,16,Fachieved this week."
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@TO]
