OL,3,CUS state visit risk 'grasped in both
OL,4,Chands' by King, aide says
OL,6,FThe New York Times said: "Beneath King
OL,7,FCharles's jokes and decorum, some
OL,8,Fsubtle rebuttals to Trump, King
OL,9,FCharles III gently pushed back against
OL,10,FPresident Trump's attacks on Britain
OL,11,Fand Nato, and he spoke of the
OL,12,Fimportance of checks and balances."
OL,14,FThe aide conceded it was a "high-
OL,15,Fstakes address to Congress" and went
OL,16,Fon to say: "First, what the King says
OL,17,Fwill always be guided by the truth.
OL,18,FTwo, it will be guided by conscience.
OL,26,@nD@ZOUtD@cO]vD@\OUwD@[O]xD@LOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/15
