OL,3,CUS state visit risk 'grasped in both
OL,4,Chands' by King, aide says
OL,6,FThe aide added: "The King is there to
OL,7,Fsupport the Government, to help the
OL,8,FGovernment. It was at the Government's
OL,9,Frequest, of course, that he undertook
OL,10,Fthis visit.
OL,12,F"The King and the Queen have been able
OL,13,Fto help the Government in any way and
OL,14,Fto get the relationship perhaps more
OL,15,Fwidely understood by a wider number of
OL,16,Fpeople without some of the noise of
OL,17,Fcurrent affairs."
OL,26,@nD@QOUtD@AOUyD@QO]
